      Upon pick up the traveller will need to <strong>start</strong> the <strong><u>handover check list process</u></strong> by answering the <strong><u>10</u></strong> questions presented under &lsquo;<strong>My handover</strong>&rsquo; in their tekkova profile. The questions will take in to consideration the overall <strong>mechanical condition of the car</strong>, <strong>interior &amp; exterior cleanliness</strong>, <strong>paint condition, visible body damage or blemishes</strong>, <strong>fuel tank level</strong>, <strong>odometer reading</strong>, etc.
    </p>
<p>
    Once <strong>submitted</strong>, the <strong>answers</strong> to the <strong><u>10</u></strong> questions will appear right away under &lsquo;<strong>My handover</strong>&rsquo; in the <strong>host&rsquo;s</strong> tekkova profile. Once the traveller <strong>submits</strong> their answer and it is <strong>confirmed</strong> by the host, the first stage of handover is complete.
</p>
  <p>
      The car may <strong>not be driven off</strong> unless the host agrees and <strong>confirms</strong> the answers to the checklist. Then the host and traveller both in their tekkova profile under &lsquo;<strong>My bookings</strong>&rsquo; must confirm <strong>picked up</strong>. At this stage the car can be driven off.
    </p>
